    "headline": "Traffic Accidents in Reykjavík Decrease Sharply Over Two Decades",
    "lede": "Every driver's nightmare is a traffic accident. Thankfully, for residents of Reykjavík, these incidents have been decreasing significantly. In the last two decades, traffic accidents involving damage or injury have dropped by nearly half.",
    "story_blocks": [
      {
        "type": "callout",
        "body": "Traffic accidents have decreased nearly by half from 2000 to 2019.",
        "highlight_value": "47%",
        "highlight_label": "fewer accidents per 1,000 vehicles"
      },
      {
        "type": "narrative",
        "heading": "Accidents Peaked in Early 2000s, Then Plummeted",
        "body": "In the chart below, you'll see that traffic accidents per 1,000 vehicles reached their peak in 2001. After that, they steadily decreased, resulting in a 47% reduction by 2019. This trend shows a significant improvement in road safety over time.",
        "viz_index": 0
      },
      {
        "type": "narrative",
        "heading": "Dramatic Fall in Casualties Since 2000",
        "body": "Similarly, the number of injuries per 1,000 vehicles has also seen a remarkable decline. Starting at a high in the year 2000, injuries decreased by about 65% to the lowest recorded level by 2019. This is excellent news for the safety of all road users.",
        "viz_index": 3
      },
      {
        "type": "narrative",
        "heading": "Vehicle Numbers Remained High but More Stable",
        "body": "While the number of vehicles on the roads increased consistently until 2007, when it peaked, the total has since dropped slightly. Despite more vehicles, the overall trend in accidents has been downward, which indicates improved safety measures and possibly better driving behaviour.",
        "viz_index": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "narrative",
        "heading": "A Safer City for All",
        "body": "These positive trends mean a safer city for everyone. With fewer accidents and injuries, there are fewer disruptions and more peace of mind for drivers and pedestrians alike. It’s a testament to improved traffic management and public awareness initiatives."
      }
    ],
